The paper deals with developing a learning algorithm for an automated online recommendation system, which involves analyzing partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) for each item of content. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and systems and control (cs.SY).
